    "caption": "Eight eyes, eight legs, and the world's strongest natural rope.",
    "shortDescription": "Spider silk is stronger than steel of the same thickness — engineers dream about being able to make it in large quantities. Spiders have silk glands for different jobs: sticky spiral silk for trapping prey, dragline silk for moving around, and wrap silk for bundling up a catch. Fun fact: Most spiders have eight eyes, but many of them have terrible vision anyway and rely mostly on vibrations through their web."
